quotes.quote: Yes, sir?
Yes, sir.
With all due respect for the Trade Federation, the Ambassodors for the Supreme Chancellor wish to board immediately.
I don't see anything.
Captain.
Tell them we wish to board at once.
I don't sense anything.
Don't center on your anxiety, Obi-Wan. Keep your concentration here and now where it belongs.
.....but not at the expense of the moment. Be mindful of the living Force, my young Padawan.
These Federation types are cowards. The negotiations will be short.
Destroyer droids!
It's a standoff! Let's go!
Battle droids.
It's an odd play for the Trade Federation. We've got to warn the Naboo and contact Chancellor Valorum. Let's split up. Stow aboard separate ships and meet down on the planet.
Let go!
Are you brainless? You almost got us killed!
The ability to speak does not make you intelligent. Now get outta here!
That wont be necessary.
I have no time for this now...
Stay down!
You forgot to turn your power off again, didn't you?
It won't take long to recharge, but this is a lesson I hope you've learned, my young Padawan.
A local. Let's go, before more of those droids show up.
A city!  Can you take us there?
No??!
You hear that?
That's the sound of a thousand terrible things heading this way...
Much farther?
That droid army is about to attack the Naboo. We must warn them.
Then speed us on our way.
We need a transport.
Thank you for your help. We go in peace.
A transport, I hope.
Thank you, my friend.
We'll need a navigator to get us through the planet's core. This Gungan my be of help.
What is to become of Jar Jar Binks here?
He has been a great help to us. I hope the punishment will not be too severe.
We need a navigator to get us through the planet's core. I have saved Jar Jar Binks' life. He owes me what you call a "life.debt."
Your gods demand that his life belongs to me now.
You're the navigator.
Full speed ahead.
There's always a bigger fish.
Stay calm. We're not in trouble yet.
Relax.
Head for that outcropping.
Get this thing started.
Come on...
Come on, Jar Jar.
Your Highness, we are the Ambassadors, for the Supreme Chancellor.
The negotiations never took place. Your Highness, we must make contact with the republic.
Do you have transports?
That won't be a problem.  Your Highness, under the circumstances, Isuggest you come to Coruscant with us.
They will kill you if you stay.
The situation here is not what it seems. There is something else behind all this, Your Highness. There is no logic in the Federation's move here. My feelings tell me they will destroy you.
If you are to leave, Your Highness, it must be now.
I'm Ambassador for the Supreme Chancellor, and I'm taking those people to Coruscant.
We'll have to land somewhere to refuel and repair the ship.
It's controlled by the Hutts...
...It would be no different than if we landed on a system controlled by the Federation...except the Hutts aren't looking for her, which gives us an advantage.

Yor Highness, we are heading for a remote planet called Tatooine. It is a system far beyond the reach of the Trade Federation. There we will be able to make needed repairs, then travel on to Coruscant.
You must trust my judgement, Your Highness.
Land near the outskirts. We don't want to attract any attention.
Don't let them send ant transmissions. Be wary...I sense a disturbance in the Force.
No more commands from Her Highness today, Captain. This spaceport is not going to be pleasant...
I don't have time to argue. But this is not a good idea. Stay close to me.
...moisture farms for the most part, but also a few indigenous tribes and scavengers. The few spaceports like this one are havens for those who do not wish to be found...
We'll try one of the smaller dealers.
I need parts for a J-type 327 Nubian.
My droid here has a readout of what I need.
Don't touch anything.
I have 20,000 Republic dataries.
I don't have anything else.  But credits will do fine.
Credits will do fine.
We're leaving.
...Obi-Wan, you're sure there isn't anything of value left on board?
All right. Another solution will present itself. I'll check back.
Not likely. We have nothing of value, that's our problem.
Nevertheless, the boy is right...you were heading for trouble. Thank you, my young friend.
We'll hed back to our ship.
I'm Qui-Gon Jinn, and this is Jar Jar Binks.
Your son was kind enough to offer us shelter.
I have enough food for a meal.
He's a very special boy. SHMI looks at him as if he's discovered a secret.
It sounds like bait to establish a connection trace.
Either way, we're running out of time.
They have Podracing on Malastare. Very fast, very dangerous.
You must have Jedi reflexes if you race Pods.
Don't do that again.
What?
What makes you think that?
Perhaps I killed a Jedi and stole it from him.
I wish that were so...
No, I'm afraid not...
I can see there's no fooling you... You mustn't let anyone know about us...we're on our way to Coruscant, the central system in the Republic, on a very important mission, and it must be kept secret.
I believe you can, but our first job is to aquire the parts we need...
Podracing... Greed can be a powerful ally.. if it's used properly.
Your mother's right. Is there anyone friendly to the Republic who might be able to help us?
The Queen does not need to know.
My ship will be the entry fee.
It's in good order, except for the parts we need.
I have...acquired a Pod in a game of chance. "The fastest ever built."
Fifty-fifty!?! If it's going to be fifty-fifty, I suggest you front the cash for the entry. If we win, you keep all the winnings, minus the cost of the parts I need...If we lose, you keep my ship.
Either way, you win.
A ship without a power supply will not get us anywhere, and there is something about this boy...
You should be proud of your son. He gives without any thought of reward.
He has special powers.
He can see things before they happen. That's why he appears to have such quick reflexes. It is a Jedi trait.
The Force is unusally strong with him, that much is clear. Who was his father?
I'm afraid not. Had he been born in the Republic, we would have identified him early, and he would have become Jedi, no doubt...he has the way. But it's too late for him now, he's too old.
I think it's time we found out. Use this power charge.
Sit still, Annie. Let me clean this cut.
Most of them.
Not likely.
There, good as new...
Checking your blood for infections.
Go on, you have a big day tomorrow.  Goodnight.
Obi-Wan...
Make an analysis of this blood sample I'm sending you.
I need a midi-chlorian count.
What are your readings?
Here's a signal check.
That's it then.
No Jedi has.
I'm not sure.
Patience, my blue friend. You'll have your winnings before the suns set, and we'll be far away from here.
You don't think Anakin will win?
Why?
I'll take that bet.
I'll wager my new racing pod against...say...the boy and his mother.
The boy is small, he can't be worth much.
For the fastest Pod ever built?!
Both, or no bet.
The boy, then...
I'll tell you later.
Of course you will.
Are you all set, Annie?  May the Force be with you.
He's fine.
The Queen trusts my judgment, young handmaiden. You should too.
Whenever you gamble, my freind, eventually you'll lose. Bring the parts to the main hanger. I'll come by your shop later so you can release the boy.
Would you like to discuss it with the Hutts...I'm sure they can settle this.
Padme. Jar Jar, let's go, we've got to get these parts back to the ship.
I'll return the eopies by midday.
Start getting this hyperdrive generator installed. I'm going back...some unfinished business. I won't be long.
It's the boy who's responsible for getting those parts.
What's this?
Did you?
Do you still think he cheated?
Well, Annie. You know the truth... You will have to tolerate his opinion, fighting won't change it.
These are yours. We sold the Pod.
And Anakin has been freed.
You're no longer a slave.
Let's just say Watto has learned an important lesson about gambling.
Our meeting was not a coincidence. Nothing happens by accident. You are strong with the Force, but you may not be accepted by the Council.
Anakin, training to be a Jedi will not be a easy challenge. And if you succeed, it will be a hard life.
This path has been placed for you, Annie; the choice to take it is yours alone.
Then, pack your things. We haven't much time.
I tried to free your mother, Annie, but Watto wouldn't have it.
It's not nearly enough.
I will watch after him. You have my word. Will you be all right?
Probe droid. Very unusual... not like anything I've seen before. Come on.
Anakin, drop!
Annie, get to the ship! Take off! Go! Go!
I think so... that was a surpirse I wont soon forget.
I don't know... but he was well trained in the Jedi arts. My guess is he was after the Queen...
We'll be safe enough once we're in hyperspace, but I have no doubt he knows our destination.
We will be patient. Anakin Skywalker, meet Obi-Wan Kenobi.
Let's hope this hyperdrive works and Watto didn't get the last laugh.
I must speak with the Jedi Council immediately, Your Honor. The situation has become more complicated.
...my only conclusion can be that it was a Sith Lord.
With your permission, my Master. I have encountered a vergence in the Force.
A boy... his cells have the highest concentration of midi-chlorians I have seen in a life form. It is possible he was conceived by the midi-chlorians.
I don't pressume...
I request the boy be tested.
Finding him was the will of the Force...I have no doubt of that. There is too much happening here...
Anakin will become A Jedi...I promise you.
I will do what I must.
You still have much to learn, my young apprentice.
He's to be trained, then.
He is the chosen one...you must see it.
I will trin him, then. I take Anakin as my Padawan learner.
Obi-Wan is ready...
Headstrong....and he has much to learn about the living Force, but he is capabe. There is little more he will learn from me.
I brought Anakin here; he must stay in my charge. He has nowhere else to go.
From your point of view....
His fate is uncertain, not dangerous. The Council will decide Anakin's future...that should be enough for you. Now get on board! OBI-WAN reluctantly boards the Naboo spacecraft followed by ARTOO.
You won't be, Annie....I'm not allowed to train you, so I want you to watch me and be mindful...always remember, your focus determines your reality. Stay close to me and you will be safe.
Midi-chlorians are a microcopic lifeform that reside within all living cells and communicates with the Force.
In your cells. We are symbionts with the midi-chlorians.

Life forms living together for mutual advantage. Without the midi-chlorians, life could not exist, and we would have no knowledge of the Force. They continually speak to you, telling you the will of the Force.
When you learn to quiet your mind, you will hear them speaking to you.
With time and training, Annie...you will.
Your Highness, it is our pleasure to continue to serve and protect you.
I promise you, I will not let that happen.
I agree...I'm not sure what you hope to accomplish by this.
I cannot fight a war for you, Your Highness, only protect you.
Good.
The Gungans will not easily be swayed, and we cannot use our power to help her.
You have been a good apprentice. You are much wiser than Iam, Obi-Wan. I foresee you will become a great Jedi Knight.
Do you know where they are?
The Viceroy will be well guarded.
There is a possibility with this diversion many Gungans will be killed.
A well-conceived plan. However, there's great risk. The weapons on your fighters may not penetrate the shields on the control ship.
Once we get inside, Annie, you find a safe placeto hide and stay
And stay there!
I agree.
No, Annie, you stay there. Stay right where you are.
Stay in that cockpit.
We'' handle this...
It is too late...It's...
Obi-Wan promise...promise me you'll train the boy...
He is the chosen one...he will...bring balance...train him!
Yes, yes, of coarse...ahhh...as you know, our blockade is perfectly legal, and we'd be happy to recieve the Ambassador...Happy to.
What?!? What did you say?
They must be dead by now. Blast, what's left of them.
What in blazes is going on down there?
Well, not exactly, but I don't... Seal off the bridge.
I want destroyer droids up here at once!!!
Close the blast doors!!!
Impossible!! This is impossible!!
At last we're getting results.
Again you come before me, Your highness. The Federation is pleased.
I was not aware of such a failure.
I take it you know the outcome. I wonder why they bother to vote.
I know nothing about any Ambassadors...you must be mistaken.
Your Highness, we would never do anything without the approval of the Senate. You assume too much.
It's too late now.
I don't know, but we must move quickly to disrupt all communications down there.
Excellent.
The invasion is on schedule, My Lord.
The Queen has great faith the Senate will side with her.
Thank you, My Lord.
No need to report that to him, until we have something to report.
Ah, victory!
The Naboo and the Federation will forge a treaty that will legitimize our occupation here. I've been assured it will be ratified by the Senate.
Now, now, your Highness. You are not going to like what we have in store for your people. In time, their suffering will persuade you to see our point of view. Commander. Process them.
We control all the cities in the North and are searching for any other settlements...
She has disappeared, My Lord. One Naboo cruiser got pat the blockade.
My Lord, it's impossible to locate the ship. It's out of our range.
Yes, My Lord. The hologram fades off.
This is getting out of hand...now there are two of them.
When are you going to give up this pointless strike? Your Queen is lost, your people are starving, and you, Governor, are going to die, much sooner than your people, I'm afraid. Take him away!
Yes, my Lord.
Yes, my Lord, we have taken over the last pockets of primitive life forms. We are in complete control of the planet now.
Yes, my Lord.
...we've sent out patrols. We've already located their starship in the swamp....It won't be long, My Lord.
We are sending all available troops to meet this army of hers assembling near the swamp. It appears to be made up of primitives. We do not expect much resistance.
I have your approval to proceed then, My Lord.
I thought the battle was going to take place far from here...this is too close!
Your little insurrection is at an end, Your Highness. Time for you to sign the treaty...and end this pointless debate in the Senate.
After her! This one is a decoy!
Your Queen will not get away with this.
Don't be absurd. There are too few of you. It won't be long before hundreds of destroyer droids break in to rescue us.
I'm TC-14 at your service. This way, please.
I hope you honoured sirs with the most comfortable here. My master will be with you shortly.
The Ambassadors are Jedi Knights, I believe.
Oh, excuse me, so sorry.
They must be important if the Viceroy sent one of those useless protocol gearheads to greet them.
A Republic cruiser! That's trouble...don't you think?
I'm not made to think.
I have a bad feeling about this.
It's not about the mission, Master, it's somethging...elsewhere...elusive.
Master Yoda says I should be mindful of the future...
Yes, Master...how do you think the trade viceroy will deal with the chancellor's demands?
Offhand, I'd say this mission is past the negotiation stage.
They have shield generators!
It's an invisible army.
You were right about one thing, Master. The negotiations were short.
Sorry, Master, the water fried my weapon.
Yes, Master.
What's this?
When they find us, they will crush us, grind us into little pieces, then blast us into oblivion!
Don't worry, this has not been our day for warm welcomes.
After those droids take control of the surface, they will come here and take control of you.
You and the Naboo form a symbiont circle. What happens to noe of you will affect the other. You must understand this.
Master, whats a bongo?
We are short of time, Master.
Master, why do you keep dragging these pathetic life forms along with us?...Here, take over.
Why were you banished, Jar Jar?
They banished you because you're clumsy?
Give me the controls.
.....we're losing power.
Power's back.
You overdid it.
What is it?
Get up here!
That was close.
I'll take care of that. OBI-WAN heads toward the group of captured pilots.
Now stay here, and keep out of trouble.
Here, Master. Tatooine... It's small, out of the way, poor... The Trade Federation has no presence there.
It's risky...but there's no alternative.
Tahyt's it. Tatooine.
Sorry, Qui-Gon's right. You'll make things less obvious.
The Hyperdrive generator is gone. We will need a new one.
I fell it also, Master.
A few containers of supplies, the Queen's wardrobe, maybe. Not enough for you to barter with. Not in the ammounts you're talking about.
This storm's going to slow them down.
It's a trick. Send no reply... Send no transmission of any kind.
...the Queen is upset...but absolutly no reply was sent.
What if it is true and the people are dying?
What if this plan fails, Master? We could be stuck here for a long time.
Yes, Master.
Wait a minute...
All right. I've got it.
Something must be wrong with the transmission.
Strange. The transmission seems to be in good order, but the reading's off the chart...over twenty thousand.
Even Master Yoda doesn't have a midi-chlorian count that high!
What does it mean?
Why do I sense we've picked up another pathetic life form...?
Over there! Fly low!
What was it?
The boy will not pass the Council's tests, Master, and you know it. He is far too old.
Don't defy the Council, Master..not again.
Master, you could be sitting on the Council by now if you would just follow the code. They will not go along with you this time.
Iam ready to face the trials.
It is not disrespect, Master, it is the truth.
The boy is dangerous...they all sense it. Why can't you?
The war's over...No need for it now.
A droid control ship.
We haven't much time.
Jar Jar is on his way to the Gungan city, Master.
Do you think the Queen's idea will work?
I'm...I'm sorry for my behavior, Master. It is not my place to disagree with you about the boy. I am grateful you think I am ready for the trials.
More likely they were wiped out.
And there's an even bigger danger. If the Vicroy escapes, Your Highness, he will return with another droid army.
Master! Master!
No!
Yes, Master...
Qui-Gon believed in him. I believe in Qui-Gon.
Master Yoda, Igave Qui-Gon my word. I will train Anakin. Without the approval of the Council if I must.
He is one with the Force, Anakin...You must let go.
I am your Master now. You will become a Jedi, I promise.
I knew it! They were sent to force a settlement, eh. Blind me, we're done for!
Impossible!! I don't...
Not sure exactly what...
Have you ever encountered a Jedi Knight before, sir?
That won't be enough, sir.
We will not survive this.
...They're still coming through!
Where are those destroyer droids?!
We have them on the run, sir...they're no match for destroyer droids.
It's Queen Amidala herself.
She's right, the Senate will never....
Do you think she suspects an attack?
...and there is no trace of the Jedi. They may have gotton onto one of your landing craft.
You didn't tell him about the missing Jedi?
We should not have made this bargain. What will happen when the Jedi become aware of these Sith Lords?
A Sith lord here with us?!!
What is going on?
Switch to bio...There they are!
Sir, they've gone up the ventilation shaft.
Sir, a transmission from the planet.
Sir, we're losing power... There is some problem with the main reactor...
You will not be pleased when you hear what I have to say, Viceroy...Your trade boycott of our planet has ended.
I have word that the Senate is finally voting on this blockade of yours.
Enough of this pretense, Viceroy! I'm aware the Chancellor's Ambassadors are with you now, and that you have beencommanded to reach a settlement.
Beware, Viceroy....the Federation is going too far this time.
We will see.
Senator Palpatine?!?  What's happening?
Don't jump to conclusions, Governor. The Federation would not dare go that far.
We must continue to rely on negotiation.
I will not condone a course of action that will lead us to war.
I will not co-operate.
Thank you, Ambassador, but my place is here with my people.
Either choice presents a great risk...to all of us...
We are brave, Your Highness.
Then, I will plead our case before the Senate.  Be careful, Governor.
It is to be commended...what is its number?
Thank you, Artoo Detoo. You have proven to be very loyal...Padme!
Continue, Captain.
That's all right.
Thank you. This little guy is quite a mess.
I've been trained in defense... I can take care of myself.
....like us. JAR JAR is in a constant state of panic.
What?
I've never heard of angels.
You're a funny little boy. How do you know so much?
You're...a slave?
I'm sorry. I don't fully understand. This is a strange world to me.
I'm glad I met you,....ah...
Anakin.
Padme Naberrie.
And that works for you.
On the outskirts.
...and our droid, Artoo-Detoo.
He's wonderful!
He's perfect.
I can't believe there is still slavery in the galaxy. The Republic's anti-slavery laws...
Our ship was damaged, and we're stranded here until we can repair it.
These junk dealers must have a weakness of some kind.
I'm sure Qui-Gon doesn't want to put your son in danger. We will find another way...
Are you sure about this? Trusting our fate to a boy we hardly know. The Queen will not approve.
Well, I don't approve.
I hope you're about finished.
I hope not; I hate fighting. Your mother wants you to come in and clean up. We have to leave soon. ANAKIN stands up and stretches just as
He and Jar Jar left already. They're with Watto at the arena.
Do what?
You've never won a race?
Not even finished?!
You carry all our hopes.
You Jedi are far too reckless. The Queen...
You assume too much.
Here he comes!
We owe you everything.
He's a friend.
Are you all right?
You're from a warm planet, Annie. Too warm for my taste. Space is cold.
The Queen is...worried. Her people are suffering...dying. She must convince the Senate to intervene, or...I'm not sure what will happen.
It's beautiful, but I don't need this to remember you. Many things will change when we reach the capital, Annie. My caring for you will always remain.
...You miss your mother.
I am grateful for your concern, Chancellor.
Chancellor Valorum seems to think there is hope.
What options do we have?
He has been our strongest supporter. Is there any other way?
There's no time for that. The courts take even longer to decide things than the Senate. Our people are dying, Senator...more and more each day. We must do something quickly to stop the Federation.
There is something I cannot do.
Who is it?
I've sent Padme on an errand.
We will tell her for you. We're sure her heart goes with you.
I wish I had your confidence in this, Senator.
You truely believe Chancellor Valorum will not bring our motion to a vote?

Honorable representatives of the Republic, distinguished delegates, and Your Honor Supreme Chancellor Valorum, I come to you under the gravest of circumstances. The Naboo system has been invaded by force. Invaded...against all the laws of the Republic by the Droid Armies of the Trade...

I will not defer...I have come before you to resolve this attack on our sovereignty now. I was not elected to watch my people suffer and die while you discuss this invasion in a committee. If this body is not capable of action, I suggest new leadership is needed. I move for a "vote of no confidence"...in Chancellor Valorum's leadership.
To motivate us, I imagine...
I don't know.
I hope not.
Who else can be nominated?
I fear by the time you have control of the bureaucrats, Senator, there will be nothing left of our cities, our people, our way of life...
With the Senate in transition, there is nothing more I can do here...Senator, this is your arena. I feel I must return to mine. I have decided to go back to Naboo. My place is with my people.
I will sign no treaty, Senator. My fate will be no different from that of our people. Captain!
Ready my ship!

No place is safe, if the Senate doesn't condemn this invasion. It is clear to me now that the Republic no longer functions as a democracy. If you win the election, Senator, I know you will do everything possible to stop the Federation. I pray you will bring sanity and compassion back to the Senate.
I welcome your help. Senator Palpatine fears the Federation means to destroy me.
I'm going to take back what's ours.
Jar Jar Binks!
Yes. I need your help.
Annie! What are you doing here?
This is going to be dangerous, Annie.
To war, I'm afraid. The Queen has had to make the most difficuld decision of her life. She doesn't believe in fighting, Annie. We are a peaceful people...
I am Queen Amidala of the Naboo...I come before you in peace.
We wish to form an alliance...
Your Honor...
I am Queen Amidala  This is my decoy...my protection...my loyal bodyguard.

...I am sorry for my deception, but under the circumstances it has become necessary to protect myself. Although we do not always agree, Your Honor, our two great societies have always lived in peace...until now. The Trade Federation has destroyed all that we have worked so hard to build. You are in hiding, my people are in camps. If we do not act quickly, all will be lost forever...I ask you to help us...no, I beg you to help us.
We are your humble servants...our fate is in your hands.
What is the situation?

The battle is a diversion. The Gungans must draw the Droid Army away from the cities. We can enter the city using the secret passages on the waterfall side. Once we get to the main entrance, Captain Pnaka will create a diversion, so that we can enter the palace and capture the Viceroy. Without the Viceroy, they will be lost and confused.
What do you think, Master Jedi?

We have a plan which should immobilize the Droid Army. We will send what pilots we have to knock out the Droid control ship which is orbiting the planet. If we can get past their rayshields, we can sever communication and their droids will be helpless.
That is why we must not fail to get to the Viceroy. Everything depends on it.
Get to your ships!
My guess is the Viceroy is in the throne room.
We don't have time for this, Captain.
Throw down your weapons. They win this round.
Captain, I said throw down your weapons.
Now, Viceroy, this is the end of your occupation here.
Now, Viceroy, you are going to have to go back to the Senate and explain all this.
Congratulations on youer election, Chancellor. It is so good to see you again.
Send him in.
I'm sorry, Annie. Padme is not here right now.
Anakin Skywalker, to see Padme, Your Highness.
A malfunction?
A communications disruption can only mean one thing. Invasion.
Negotiation? We've lost all communications!...and where atre the Chancellors Ambassadors? How can we negotiate? We must prepare to defend ourselves.
...how will you explain this invasion to the Senate?
Your negotiations seem to have failed, Ambassador.
They wouldn't dare.
Please, Your Highness, reconsider. Our only hope is for the Senate to side with us... Senator Palpatine will need your help.
Your Highness, I will stay here and do what I can...They will have to retain the Council of Governors in order to maintain control. But you must leave...

...cut off all food supplies until you return...the death toll is catastrophic...we must bow to their wishes, Your Highness...Please tell us what to do! If you can hear us, Your Highness, you must contact me... AMIDALA looks upset...almost nervous.
This invasion will gain you nothing. We're a democracy. The people have decided... They will not live under your tyranny.
...How could that be true? I have assurances from the Chancellor...his Ambassadors did arrive. It must be the...get...negotiate...
It is a great gift to see you alive, Your Majesty. May I present Supreme Chancellor Valorum.
There is a question of precedure, but I feel confident we can overcome it...

...the Republic is not what it once was. The Senate is full of greedy, squabbling delegates who are only looking out for themselves and their home sytems. There is no interest in the common good...no civility, only politics...its disgusting. I must be frank, Your Majesty, there is little chance the Senate will act on the invasion.
If I may say so, Your Majesty, the Chancellor has little real power...he is mired down by baseless accusations of corruption. A manufactured scandal surrounds him. The bureaucrats are in charge now.

Our best choice would be to push for the election of a stronger Supreme Chancellor. One who will take control of the bureaucrats, enforces the laws, and give us justice. You could call for a vote of no confidence in Chancellor Valorum.
Our only other choice would to be to submit a plea to the courts...
To be realistic, Your Highness, I'd say we're going to have to accept Federation control for the time being.
If the Federation moves to defer the motion...Your Majesty, Ibeg of you to ask for a resolution to end this congressional session.
You must force a new election for Supreme Chancellor...I promise you there are many who will support us...it is our best chance... Your Majesty, our only, chance.
He is distracted...he is afraid. He will be of no help.
